359
00:23:51,440 --> 00:23:54,398
Did you tell them he might get killed
if they find him on the streets?

360
00:23:54,520 --> 00:23:56,476
Milly, I did everything I could.

361
00:23:56,600 --> 00:24:00,275
No, you did what you're comfortable
doing. You made one phone call.

362
00:24:00,680 --> 00:24:02,636
You need to act
like you're not afraid to act.

363
00:24:02,760 --> 00:24:05,479
- I'm not afraid to act.
- So prove it.

364
00:24:06,320 --> 00:24:08,595
Your breath smells like whiskey.

365
00:24:26,280 --> 00:24:27,554
Peter.

366
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:32,308
What're they doing down at spy central,
you're hanging out here?

367
00:24:32,680 --> 00:24:37,071
I can't help your friend, Mort.
Excuse me. I'll have a merlot, please.

368
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:42,076
- Sorry, sir. Tonight we have cabernet.
- Excellent. I will have a merlot.

369
00:24:47,680 --> 00:24:49,955
There's the ambassador.
Why not try her?

370
00:24:55,160 --> 00:24:56,195
Thanks.

371
00:24:57,920 --> 00:25:00,115
- I'll be sure to tell her.
- Thanks, I will.

372
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:01,958
- Nice to see you.
- You, too.

373
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:05,637
Thank you so much
for having us this evening. Thank you.

374
00:25:05,760 --> 00:25:08,320
- Madame Ambassador.
- Mr Kondracke.

375
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:11,273
I've been told to avoid you this evening.
Nice to see you.

376
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:14,119
Thank you. You got...
We have a bit of a situation here...

377
00:25:14,240 --> 00:25:18,518
and I think if I have to write it up, it's not
going to look good as an obituary.

378
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:20,674
I see.

379
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:24,152
- I gave it...
